South Africa’s net foreign reserves rose to $45.147 billion in January from $44.89 billion in December, Reserve Bank data showed on Friday. But gross reserves slipped, deceasing to $54.613 billion at the end of January from $55.05 billion in the previous month. The forward position, representing the central bank’s unsettled or swap transactions, swung to a positive balance of $547 million in January after a negative balance of $64 million previously.